A very common situation where digital communication fails is when a student sends an email or message that lacks clarity and an appropriate tone. For example, a student might message a professor on WhatsApp in a vague or abrupt way, such as saying, “Send notes fast.” Such wording can come across as rude or disrespectful to the professor.

This type of communication issue could be avoided by following proper etiquette. Using appropriate communication practices would encourage the student to include context, such as greeting the professor, making the request politely, and expressing gratitude. Additionally, choosing the correct platform for communication is also an important aspect of effective digital interaction.
